            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1948-10-15T21:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1948-10-15T21:00:00-05:00" n="746" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d746">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">393.1115/10–1348: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of State</gloss> to
                        the Ambassador in China</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Stuart</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1948-10-15T21:00:00-05:00">October 15, 1948—9 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1457. Dept assumes you will notify it as soon as you instruct Consulates to issue
                    warning (your 1896, Oct 13) so that it will be in position to answer numerous
                    inevitable press inquiries this regard. In informing Dept Emb should include
                    text warning, specific reasons therefor and date and time of release. Dept also
                    desires earliest info giving estimates ConGens Peiping Tientsin re probable
                    percentage American residents who will act on formal warning to evacuate.</p>
                <p>For Emb info, on receipt notification issuance formal warning evacuate north
                    China, Dept will cease issuance passports to all persons proceeding that area
                    other than Govt officials or in extraordinary cases.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lovett</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
